@Ovilia First, to deal with default color. Should I just check the type or directly get `itemModel.option.color`?
When `option.color` is string, `data.getVisual('color')` is the same as `itemModel.get('color')`
```js
var color = typeof itemModel.get('color') === 'string' 
    ? itemModel.get('color') 
    : data.getVisual('color')
```
Second, it also can be useful when I only need to set various `line.lineStyle.color` and `line.ItemStyle.color`. In that case, the legend color will be `red`, but I want it is `blue`:
```
option = {
  legend: {
    backgroundColor: "rgba(0,100,50,0.2)"
  },
  tooltip: {},
  xAxis: {
    data: ['test', 'test2']
  },
  yAxis: {
    splitArea: {
      show: true
    }
  },
  series: {
    type: "line",
    name: "test",
    data: [
        20,
        30
    ],
    lineStyle: {
      color: "blue"
    },
    itemStyle: {
      color: "red"
    }
  }
};
```
